	1️⃣ What is Virtualization?
	✅ Definition:
	Virtualization is a technology that allows multiple virtual machines (VMs) to run on a single physical server by sharing hardware resources like CPU, RAM, storage, and network.
	🔹 Simple Example:
	One physical server → 5 virtual servers (Linux, Windows, DB, App)
	
	2️⃣ Benefits of Virtualization
	🔹 Advantages:
		• Better hardware utilization
		• Cost reduction (less servers)
		• Faster server deployment
		• Isolation between VMs
		• Easy backup & recovery
		• Scalability
		• High availability
	📌 Interview Line:
		Virtualization helps run multiple isolated OS on one physical machine efficiently.
	
	3️⃣ What is a Virtual Machine (VM)?
	✅ Definition:
	A VM is a software-based computer that runs an operating system and applications just like a physical machine.
	🔹 Characteristics:
		• Has its own OS
		• Has virtual CPU, RAM, Disk
		• Isolated from other VMs
		• Created using a hypervisor
	
	4️⃣ What is a Hypervisor?
	✅ Definition:
	A hypervisor is software that creates, manages, and runs virtual machines by allocating physical hardware resources.
	
	5️⃣ Types of Hypervisors
	🔹 Type 1 – Bare Metal Hypervisor
		• Runs directly on hardware
		• High performance
		• More secure
		• Used in data centers
	Examples:
		• VMware ESXi
		• Microsoft Hyper-V
		• Xen
	
	🔹 Type 2 – Hosted Hypervisor
		• Runs on top of an OS
		• Easy to install
		• Less performance
	Examples:
		• VMware Workstation
		• VirtualBox
	
	6️⃣ Difference: Bare Metal vs Hosted Hypervisor
	Feature	Bare Metal	Hosted
	Runs on	Hardware	Operating System
	Performance	High	Lower
	Security	High	Medium
	Use case	Production	Testing/Lab
	
	7️⃣ Difference between Cloud Models (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS)
	🔹 IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)
		• You manage OS & apps
		• AWS manages hardware
	Examples:
		• AWS EC2
		• Azure VM
	
	🔹 PaaS (Platform as a Service)
		• OS & runtime managed by provider
		• You deploy code
	Examples:
		• AWS Elastic Beanstalk
		• Azure App Service
	
	🔹 SaaS (Software as a Service)
		• Fully managed application
	Examples:
		• Gmail
		• Office 365
		• Salesforce
	
	8️⃣ What is an Availability Zone (AZ)?
	✅ Definition:
	An Availability Zone is a physically separate data center within an AWS region.
	🔹 Purpose:
		• High availability
		• Fault tolerance
		• Disaster recovery
	📌 Interview Tip:
